postcontent: Here is a nice classic Remington Derringer Over/Under in .41caliber. This one is the "Type III" with the marking of "REMINGTON ARMS -- UMC CO, ILLION, NY" on the barrel rib. The firing pin is cool as each time you cock the hammer, the firing pin moves up or down to the next barrel. The trigger pull is smooth and the hammer drops with authority. I see no reason why it can't be fired and enjoyed at the range or for self defense conceal carry - if you use the appropriate ammo in this baby. There is a shell ejector on the left side of the barrel and it works smoothly with no sticking. Then plastic grips are in great shape with no cracks.
